com.davidsoergel.trees.dhtpn

Interface ResultCollector

  • All Superinterfaces:
    DoubleHierarchicalTypedProperties<Integer,String,String,Serializable,ResultCollector,SerializableHierarchicalTypedPropertyNode<String,Serializable>>, HierarchyNode<HierarchicalTypedPropertyNode<String,Serializable,SerializableHierarchicalTypedPropertyNode<String,Serializable>>,ResultCollector>, Iterable<ResultCollector>, Serializable, SerializableDoubleHierarchicalTypedProperties<ResultCollector>

    public interface ResultCollector
extends SerializableDoubleHierarchicalTypedProperties<ResultCollector>
    A container for all of the results produced by a JobThread. The outer hierarchy layer corresponds to the ParameterSet hierarchy. The idea is that a single JobThread may produce a number of ParameterSet nodes, each corresponding to a replicate experiment, or to a different value of some parameter that is being swept over, etc. The inner hierarchy layer corresponds to the set of key-value pairs within a single ParameterSet. The keys may be hierarchically organized for symmetry with the input side, but in practice that will rarely be necessary.
